op:0;\">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">What’s the difference between melamine and porcelain whiteboard surfaces?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Melamine surfaces are budget-friendly but wear and ghost (leave faint marker residue) faster with heavy daily use; porcelain (often called \"ceramic steel\") surfaces cost more but resist ghosting and staining much better over years of frequent use.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Do magnetic whiteboards work the same as non-magnetic ones for writing?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Yes - magnetic capability is an added feature (usually a steel backing) that doesn’t affect the writing/erasing surface itself, so a magnetic whiteboard writes and erases the same as a non-magnetic one while also letting you attach magnets and papers.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">What size whiteboard is appropriate for a home office versus a meeting room?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">A small 2x3 ft board suits a home office or personal planning space; a meeting room or classroom setting typically needs 4x6 ft or larger for content to be visible from across the room.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">How do I prevent ghosting on a whiteboard over time?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Ghosting (permanent faint marks) is reduced by erasing markers promptly rather than letting them sit for days, using quality dry-erase markers rather than permanent markers by mistake, and occasionally cleaning with a dedicated whiteboard cleaner rather than plain water.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><em>As an Amazon Associate, ChampionsReviews.com earns from qualifying purchases. All prices, ratings, and review counts shown are pulled directly from Amazon.com listings at the time of publishing and are subject to change. Pros, cons, and recommendations above are editorial analysis based on this listed data, not independent hands-on testing.</em></p>\n"
